---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service -- 24K Labs" description="Terms of Service for 24K Labs AI code analysis services.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header__glow"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="page-header__badge">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="page-header__desc">
        The short version: use the service, pay for it, don't be weird about it.
        Here's the long version.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose reveal">

        <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> April 9, 2026</p>

        <h2>What 24K Labs Is</h2>
        <p>
          24K Labs provides AI-powered code analysis services accessed via API.
          You send us code, our AI analyzes it, you get results back. That's the product.
        </p>

        <h2>What You Get</h2>
        <p>
          When you make a request, you receive AI-generated analysis based on the code you submit.
          Results vary depending on the model tier you select (Haiku, Sonnet, or Opus) and the
          complexity of your code. Different tiers offer different depth of analysis at different price points.
        </p>

        <h2>No Warranty on AI Output</h2>
        <p>
          Let's be direct: AI can make mistakes. The output you receive is <strong>advisory, not guaranteed</strong>.
          It's a tool, not a replacement for your own judgment. You are responsible for reviewing and
          validating any results before acting on them.
        </p>
        <p>
          We work hard to make the analysis useful and accurate, but we don't warrant that
          every response will be correct, complete, or suitable for your specific use case.
        </p>

        <h2>Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>All prices are in USD. We currently support one payment method with another on the way:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>x402 (live now):</strong> USDC on Base L2. Payments are final on-chain and non-reversible.
            This is the native web3 payment rail -- your wallet pays, the service responds.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Stripe (coming soon):</strong> Standard credit card processing for those who prefer traditional payments.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Refund Policy</h2>
        <p>
          Not satisfied? Email <a href="mailto:support@24klabs.ai">support@24klabs.ai</a> within
          <strong>24 hours</strong> of your request for a full refund.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Refunds are issued at 24K Labs' discretion.</li>
          <li>x402 refunds are processed manually to the wallet address that made the payment.</li>
          <li>Stripe refunds are processed back to the original payment method.</li>
          <li>Demo (free) requests are not eligible for refunds -- because they're free.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>Don't do these things:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Don't submit malicious code designed to attack our systems.</li>
          <li>Don't use the service for illegal purposes.</li>
          <li>Don't attempt to reverse-engineer our prompts or models.</li>
          <li>Don't abuse the API with automated spam requests.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If we determine you're violating these rules, we reserve the right to block your access
          without refund.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Handling</h2>
        <p>
          Code you submit is processed by Claude (Anthropic's API) and is subject to
          <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/policies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic's usage policies</a>.
          We log request metadata -- timestamps, service used, tokens consumed -- but we
          <strong>do not permanently store your submitted code</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for the full picture.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          24K Labs' total liability is limited to the amount you paid for the specific request
          in question. We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages
          arising from your use of the service.
        </p>
        <p>
          Translation: if our AI gives you bad advice and you ship it to production without reviewing it,
          that's on you. Our maximum exposure is the cost of the request.
        </p>

        <h2>Service Availability</h2>
        <p>
          We aim for high availability but don't guarantee 100% uptime. Services may be
          interrupted for maintenance, upgrades, or things outside our control. We'll do our
          best to keep downtime minimal and communicate about planned maintenance.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms as the service evolves. We'll note the effective date at the top.
          Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, United States.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms? Email us at
          <a href="mailto:support@24klabs.ai">support@24klabs.ai</a>.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
